Good game but if you leave the time section open long enough the x button disapears
replyContent:
Hi Josh, this is the intended effect. After a time all the windows will autolock, ie, the 'x' and tab will disappear to save screen space. To unlock again, pls hold the top-right btn for 2 secs, and you will be able to modify again. 
You can turn off this autolock feature in Config. 
Hope that helps!

content: EASILY THE BEST ANDROID SPACEFLIGHT SIM  Nvidia Shield Portable user here. Outstanding graphics. Hugely ambitious simulator. Unfortunately the game is a little buggy at present, which is to be expected with such an ambitious project, at such an early stage, on such a limited platform,  however this should certainly not deter any enthusiastic, budding astronauts out there.   I would like to see the addition of a facility that would allow the player to plot a course to another planet efficiently and without error as this is very difficult at present. It is entirely possible of course that the facility may already exist and I simply haven't found the way yet. Is this the case? I would also love to see higher detail graphics while at the ground level such as buildings etc  After all major bugs have been fixed I will certainly be revising my 4 star review to a higher score. Thank you so much for this game.
Need to explain more the controls of the spaceships
replyContent: hi Mateo. We are working now 100% towards a user-frienly user guide , explaining the controls, autopilot , spacecraft specs, etc..  Thanks
